      <hedline>
        <hl1>Fly the Angry Skies</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Jeff MacGregor's amusing analysis of the state of American air travel misses one important point (The Way We Live Now, Sept. 24). Air travel has lost its appeal because it's now available to everyone. Modern planes are nothing more than flying buses. Your fellow passengers are now the same ones who, years ago, made you swear you'd never ride a Greyhound again.</p>
        <p>David J. Martin  Ottawa</p>
      </block>
